A1: (not ( [#] X ) in ( [#] X ));
A2: ( [#] ( One-Point_Compactification X ) ) = ( succ ( [#] X ) ) by CKB29:def 1;
( [#] X ) in { ( [#] X ) } by TARSKI:def 1;
then reconsider q = ( [#] X ) as (Point of ( One-Point_Compactification X )) by A2,XBOOLE_0:def 3;
A3: (the topology of ( One-Point_Compactification X )) = ( (the topology of X) \/ D ) by CKB29:def 1;
A4: ( [#] X ) c= ( [#] ( One-Point_Compactification X ) ) by CKB31:1;
thus (X is  Hausdorff  locally-compact implies ( One-Point_Compactification X ) is  Hausdorff)
proof
assume that
A5: X is  Hausdorff
and
A6: X is  locally-compact;
let p being (Point of ( One-Point_Compactification X ));
