then consider W,V being (Subset of X) such that A8: W is  open and A9: V is  open and A10: p in W and A11: q in V and A12: W misses V by A5,A7,PRE_TOPC:def 10;
reconsider W,V as (Subset of ( One-Point_Compactification X )) by A4,XBOOLE_1:1;
V in (the topology of X) by A9,PRE_TOPC:def 2;
then A13: V in (the topology of ( One-Point_Compactification X )) by A3,XBOOLE_0:def 3;
take W;
take V;
W in (the topology of X) by A8,PRE_TOPC:def 2;
then W in (the topology of ( One-Point_Compactification X )) by A3,XBOOLE_0:def 3;
hence (W is  open & V is  open) by A13,PRE_TOPC:def 2;
